Using Bootstrap in Prj
----------------------
Include these lines in the <head>

<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">

Include the CSS files in the <head>

<link href="css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"> 
<link href="css/bootstrap-theme.min.css" rel="stylesheet">

Include the jquery library and the javascript functions towards the end of the body as Bootstrap is dependent on it.
It is included before the end of the body, cause the page can be rendered even before the Javascript is actually processed;
So when the web page is rendered by the browser, it'll first display all the content and then use the Javascript tp restyle the content;
This make web page loading faster;

Boostrap Container Class
------------------------
<div class="container">....</div>
Container -> Class to hold all the contents of our web page. The container defines the fixed width regions within your web page;
Inside it contents that will be displayed for your web pages.
* .container-fluid class allows full width container;

Bootstrap Rows
---------------
<div class="row">....</div>
-> Divides the page into multiple rows.
-> Rows act as horizontal grouping for columns.
-> Rows must be inside containers;

Bootstrap Jumbotron -> top line;
-------------------------
<div class="jumbotron">....</div>
- Light-weight, flexible components for showcasing key content; 
- Can be used outside a container to span the entire screen width;



